{"id": 221346465, "abstract": "We propose a nonparametric extension to the factor analysis problem using a beta process prior. This beta process factor analysis (BP-FA) model allows for a dataset to be decomposed into a linear combination of a sparse set of factors, providing information on the underlying structure of the observations. As with the Dirichlet process, the beta process is a fully Bayesian conjugate prior, which allows for analytical posterior calculation and straightforward inference. We derive a varia-tional Bayes inference algorithm and demonstrate the model on the MNIST digits and HGDP-CEPH cell line panel datasets.", "cluster": "4", "citations": [290390475, 282000655, 269873317, 274263431, 273888737, 265052287, 261404006, 269164447, 260439271, 260623423], "references": [34000771, 220320786, 220321011, 229100417, 221619194, 2522345, 220848162, 224514581, 38359431, 10980474], "authors": ["John William Paisley", "Lawrence Carin"], "title": "Nonparametric factor analysis with Beta process priors"}